Full Tang Brown Natural Ebony Wooden Handle : Ergonomic Full Tang handle can prevent the blade comfortable to grip and non-slip effect. The kitchen cleaver butcher knife is a impeccable performance this strong design with a good strength, durability. All-Purpose Kitchen Knife Cleaver : The Grandsharp chef knife is perfect for breaking down larger cuts of boneless meat and light bone poultry as well as dicing, mincing and chopping tough vegetables and fruits. Perfect Cutting Edges : Incredible sharp edge with 15°angle per side for peak performance handling kitchen tasks,curved blade for efficient chopping. Regarding the cutting techniques, you just need to hold the cleaver tightly with one hand and apply some weight with the other hand on the spine to cut through thick chunks of meat and hard vegetable. Unique Forged Pattern 8'' Chef Knives use repeated folding and flapping methods to make the blade ultra sharp.And meat cleaver knives are sharpened manually by experienced workers by using natural knife grinders mined,Compared with knife made with mechanical ways, the service life of such classical chef knife is longer. Ergonomic Ebony wooden Handle will bring you a superior hand control, agility and comfort. Never fatigue because of prolonged use caused to the palm or wrist. It is a perfect chef knife for people who frequently use for cooking or who like the kitchen.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 24, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very Nice, Sharp and Perfect for Food Prep.
reviews.reviewText: I’m a tool guy. I have often researched and tried many edged tools for carpentry, wood carving, camping, cooking, EDC, and just for personal preference – before settling on a design and specifications that I feel works the best, at least for me. Several years ago, I discovered this Serbian style of chef knife, and found it delightful for all-around kitchen and camp use. This “Grand Sharp” 8-inch model (edge is actually 7 7/8”) is a great fit and exceptional at its price point. Some Japanese- and Chinese- “cleaver” type knives can cost several hundreds of dollars and won't exceed this tool’s utility. It is well balanced, and has a useful edge curve. The 56 Rockwell hardness is perfect for maintaining its very sharp edge. This is not intended to be a heavy meat cleaver; but with its thin profile and attractive “hand hammered” appearance, it is perfect for mincing, chopping and cutting ingredients. The leather sheath will go well with my camp gear, and make this a favorite outdoors barbeque and camp chef tool. It does everything a basic chef's knife does, plus it adds extra surface area and spine for food handling convenience. I like it!
